# Backend Schema Documentation: CAFE co. Web Application

**Document Version:** 1.0
**Date:** May 2, 2026
**Author:** Manus AI

## 1. Introduction

This document details the backend database schema for the CAFE co. web application. The schema is designed to support the functional requirements outlined in the Product Requirements Document (PRD), ensuring efficient storage and retrieval of data for reservations, inquiries, event leads, menu items, and shop products. The database will primarily utilize PostgreSQL or SQLite.

## 2. Database Tables

### 2.1. `bookings` Table

This table stores information related to customer reservations made through the website.

| Field Name       | Data Type      | Constraints      | Description                                     |
| :--------------- | :------------- | :--------------- | :---------------------------------------------- |
| `booking_id`     | UUID / INTEGER | PRIMARY KEY      | Unique identifier for each booking              |
| `name`           | VARCHAR(255)   | NOT NULL         | Full name of the person making the reservation  |
| `email`          | VARCHAR(255)   | NOT NULL         | Email address of the person making the reservation |
| `guest_count`    | INTEGER        | NOT NULL, > 0    | Number of guests for the reservation            |
| `table_location` | VARCHAR(50)    | NOT NULL         | Preferred table location (e.g., Indoor, Bar, Patio) |
| `reservation_date` | DATE           | NOT NULL         | Date of the reservation                         |
| `reservation_time` | TIME           | NOT NULL         | Time of the reservation                         |
| `created_at`     | TIMESTAMP      | DEFAULT NOW()    | Timestamp when the booking was created          |

**Conflict-Check Logic:** Before inserting a new booking, the system will check for existing reservations at the same `reservation_date`, `reservation_time`, and `table_location` to prevent double-booking. Further logic can be implemented to manage table capacity.

### 2.2. `inquiries` Table

This table stores messages submitted through the contact form.

| Field Name       | Data Type      | Constraints      | Description                                     |
| :--------------- | :------------- | :--------------- | :---------------------------------------------- |
| `inquiry_id`     | UUID / INTEGER | PRIMARY KEY      | Unique identifier for each inquiry              |
| `subject`        | VARCHAR(255)   | NOT NULL         | Subject of the inquiry                          |
| `message`        | TEXT           | NOT NULL         | Full message content                            |
| `user_contact_info` | VARCHAR(255)   | NOT NULL         | Contact information of the user (e.g., email, phone) |
| `timestamp`      | TIMESTAMP      | DEFAULT NOW()    | Timestamp when the inquiry was submitted        |
| `status`         | VARCHAR(50)    | DEFAULT 'New'    | Status of the inquiry (e.g., New, In Progress, Resolved) |

### 2.3. `event_leads` Table

This table captures detailed information for event booking inquiries from the Celebration Hub.

| Field Name       | Data Type      | Constraints      | Description                                     |
| :--------------- | :------------- | :--------------- | :---------------------------------------------- |
| `lead_id`        | UUID / INTEGER | PRIMARY KEY      | Unique identifier for each event lead           |
| `event_type`     | VARCHAR(100)   | NOT NULL         | Type of event (e.g., Birthday, Anniversary, Corporate) |
| `estimated_budget` | DECIMAL(10, 2) | NULLABLE         | Estimated budget for the event                  |
| `add_ons`        | TEXT           | NULLABLE         | Comma-separated list of requested add-ons (e.g., Live Music, Catering, Decor) |
| `lead_status`    | VARCHAR(50)    | DEFAULT 'New'    | Current status of the event lead (e.g., New, Contacted, Quoted, Booked) |
| `contact_name`   | VARCHAR(255)   | NOT NULL         | Name of the event organizer                     |
| `contact_email`  | VARCHAR(255)   | NOT NULL         | Email of the event organizer                    |
| `contact_phone`  | VARCHAR(50)    | NULLABLE         | Phone number of the event organizer             |
| `event_date`     | DATE           | NULLABLE         | Preferred date for the event                    |
| `guest_count`    | INTEGER        | NULLABLE         | Estimated number of guests                      |
| `notes`          | TEXT           | NULLABLE         | Any additional notes or special requests        |
| `created_at`     | TIMESTAMP      | DEFAULT NOW()    | Timestamp when the lead was created             |

